helpTip: The date when the project was started.

A field that can contain a value that reflects the status of tasks in the project. When creating tasks, template authors can specify a value for the Process Status field. When a task from a template is completed in the project, the template task can have been configured with a Field Setter to set the Process Status field to a new value as a result of the task completion. For example, when first created, Contract Request projects have Process Status of Needs Approval, via the initial value for the field in the project template. When the Contract Request project's Approval task completes successfully, the Process Status field is changed to be Approved.

Description of the project

A Quick Project is a sourcing event, such as an RFI, RFP, or Auction.

A Full Project is a container for a sourcing event, but adds process management functionality, such as the ability to assign tasks and collaboratively edit documents with your team members.

Your available Project types may vary depending on your configuration.
This indicates the current state of the project.  Planned indicates the project has not yet begun. The states 'On Hold', 'Completed' and 'Cancelled' will be available while editing the project.
This is the date you plan to start executing the project.  This typically is earlier than the execution of a Sourcing event.  It is used for reporting purposes only.
This is the date you plan to complete the project as opposed to the actual date when the project ends.  It is used for reporting purposes only.
Defines the type of event

A test project prepares and educates your team members and participants prior to running an actual event.

You can use the test project field as a filter when creating analytical reports.

Once sourcing project/request is created it is not possible to edit the test project field. In case of events event owner can change the value of this field in draft status and event administrators can change the value of this field after a event is published.

You can delete test projects more easily.

The system sends emails in the same way that it does in a normal event; be careful not to inadvertently send emails.
